    "summary": "Hi there, I'm Erik, happy to take a moment to introduce myself. You can find a selection of things I've done in my (semi-)professional life below. But more importantly I like to share what I enjoy doing.\n\nAfter working in sustainability consulting, startups and web development, I decided to canoe in the Amazon. This kind of worked out and it became quite a longer journey and adventure then planned. Jungle areas, plants and ecosystems grasped my attention as well as how our relation is to nature.\n\nHealth of our natural environments, traditional ways and our personal health always interested me, but it became much more after traveling and living in permaculture communities.\n\nThis led me to a new project: Pure Kakaw sparked from the fascination of how cacao was used traditionally and the benefits it has for our body & mind. Nature is an incredible source for learning, to increase our potential and live healthily.\n\nIt is a true joy to work directly with farmers in different places in Central & South America. To source a fair and healthy product, and to support agroforestry farming and planting more trees.\n\n\nSome other fields of interest:\n- Meditation\n- Permaculture\n- Mycology\n- Cacao\n- Regenerative Agroforestry",
